body:
&quot;A few light touches should get both flavors of the void puppy to a stable spot.&quot;
&quot;for mage Kog, that&rsquo;s pulling some excess waveclear out of his lane phase to keep him on his toes.&quot;

&quot;E - Void Ooze
DAMAGE 60/110/160/210/260 &rArr; 60/105/150/195/240
RATIO 0.7 ability power &rArr; 0.5 ability power&quot;

So apparently reducing the AP ratio by .2 would be one of those &quot;light touches&quot; intended to reduce his waveclear during the laning phase.  I can completely understand reducing the base because that directly hits the early game hardest, and keeps the late game fairly similar, but reducing the AP ratio by .2 is a massive hit to his mid and late game burst and waveclear.

Why can&#039;t they just take small steps when balancing other champions than just their favorites?
